      "author_association" : "MEMBER",
      "body" : "I believe that the rationale behind `std::byte` in the C++ standard is having a type that represents pure \"memory units\" for storage, without associated arithmetic. So I think it makes sense to start adopting those in our codebase whenever char/uchar are used in places that don't actually treat them as numbers or as characters of a string.",
